text: The Kuyachinsky Village Council is a municipality in Altaysky District, Altai Krai, Russia. It has the status of a rural settlement and an administrative- territorial entity. The administrative center is the village of Kuyacha. == Population == According to the 2010 All-Russian population census, the population of the municipality was 839 people.
